Thailand Stocks: Big C Supercenter, Land & Houses, Sri Trang

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-10-20T10:00:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/bangkok-first-bank-of-ayudhya-big-c-thailand-stock-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index fell for a third day, declining 3.1 percent
to 909.10, the largest drop since Oct. 3.  Property developers: KGI Securities (Thailand) Pcl
downgraded Thai residential property to “underweight” from
“overweight” to reflect the impact of the global economic
slowdown and prolonged flooding.  Land & Houses Pcl (LH TB), Thailand’s biggest home builder
by market value, slumped 9.5 percent to 5.25 baht, the steepest
decline since Dec. 1, 2008.  Asian Property Development Pcl (AP)   slipped 8.6 percent to 4.28 baht, the lowest close since
June 25, 2010.  Sansiri Pcl (SIRI)   lost 5.5 percent to 1.04
baht.  Rubber producers: Rubber in  Tokyo  plunged to a 14-month low
as a French-German split emerged over  Europe ’s rescue strategy,
deepening concern the region may fail to contain debt crisis,
hurting demand for raw materials.  Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  , Thailand’s biggest
publicly traded rubber producer, fell 5.7 percent to 16.60 baht.
Thai Rubber Latex Corp. (Thailand) Pcl (TRUBB TB) declined 1.3
percent to 2.98 baht.  Big C Supercenter Pcl (BIGC)  , an operator of hypermarket
stores, slid 13 percent to 99.75 baht, the largest drop since
February 2000. The company plans to raise as much as 25 billion
baht ($807 million) in a rights offering, it said in a statement  To contact the reporter on this story:
